        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 30 at 3:39PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 337 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms
scattered along a line extending from near Gail to Fluvanna to 7
miles south of Snyder. Movement was west at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Snyder, Ackerly, Gail, Coahoma, Fluvanna, J B Thomas Reservoir,
Lamesa Municipal Airport, Luther, Los Ybanez, Sparenberg, Vincent,
Hermleigh, Randalls Corner, Winston Field, Knapp, Cuthbert, Hancock,
Dunn, Tenmile, and Knott.

This includes Interstate 20 between mile markers 187 and 199.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with these storms.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
